    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-01-24T12:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-01-24T12:45:00-05:00" n="246"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d246">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.01/399: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-24T12:00:00-05:45"
                            >January 24, 1934—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 3 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>26. My 25, January 23, 2 p.m. Minister for Foreign Affairs Arguello who returned
                    yesterday from Montevideo informed me this morning that arrangements had been
                    definitely made with Governments of Honduras and Guatemala for recognition by
                    the three Governments of El Salvador tomorrow morning, January 25. He said that
                    to give the recognition “a more solemn character” President Sacasa <pb
                        facs="0317" n="251" xml:id="pg_251"/> will, apart from sending telegram to
                    General Martínez, issue a formal decree announcing recognition and referring to
                    adherence of Nicaragua to the principles of treaty of 1923.</p>
                <p>Dr. Arguello stated that it is probable that conference to discuss revision of
                    treaty will probably meet in Guatemala.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Guatemala and Tegucigalpa.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
